			<h4 class="blue" >2. Proper Breathing (Pranayama)</h4>
			<p class="paragraph">
				Breath is to the body what a battery is to a car. It gives us oxygen, most needed for our cells, but also gives us prana, or vital energy. Pranayama, or yogic breathing exercises, are an integral part of the Sivananda yoga practice. It increases, balances and purifies our energy system and awakens higher energy. Learning how to breath correctly allows the body and mind to move into stillness and facilitates meditation practice.
			</p>
