		<div class="span8">
			<h4 class="blue" >4. Proper Diet (Vegetarian)</h4>
			<p class="paragraph">
				Food is the fuel for the physical vehicle. Yoga is concerned with the subtle effect food has on the serenity of the mind and the keenness of the intellect, as well as the health of the body. The yogic diet is sattvic, not rajasic and tamasic. Sattvic - stable pure focused energy, calm, balanced, lively. The aim of yoga is to increase the proportion of sattvic energy in our being by choosing sattvic foods, and avoiding rajasic and tamasic foods. Hence, the yogic diet is a vegetarian one, consisting of pure, simple natural foods which are easily digested and promote health. Eating foods grown in fertile soil, free from chemicals and pesticides, ensures a better supply of nutrients to the body. Rajasic - unstable energy, restless activity, excitement, passion, and Tamasic &ndash; the lowest rate of vibration, inert, immobile, dark, lethargic, are attributes that are not included in the sattvic diet.
			</p>
		</div>
